---
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Repl from '../../../../components/Repl';
import SchemeRepl from '../../../../components/SchemeRepl';
import Neighbors from "../../../../components/Neighbors.astro";
import PrevNext from "../../../../components/PrevNext.astro";
---

<Layout title="Judson Ch.3 — Homomorphisms" favicon="🔗">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/abstract-algebra/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to algebra</a>

    <h1>Homomorphisms</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Tom Judson &middot; GFDL &middot; <a href="http://abstract.ups.edu/">Abstract Algebra: Theory and Applications, Ch. 3</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">A <strong>homomorphism</strong> is a function between groups that preserves the operation: f(a * b) = f(a) * f(b). The <strong>kernel</strong> measures what it forgets. The <strong>image</strong> measures what it hits. These three pieces tell you everything about how one group maps onto another.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- 1. Definition -->
    <h3>Structure-preserving maps</h3>
    <p>A function f: G to H is a <strong>group homomorphism</strong> if f(a *_G b) = f(a) *_H f(b) for all a, b in G. The operation on the left is G's operation; the operation on the right is H's. The function translates one group's structure into the other's without distortion.</p>

    <!-- SVG: two groups with a map between them -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 400 160" class="w-full max-w-md" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- Group G (left) -->
        <ellipse cx="90" cy="80" rx="70" ry="55" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.3"/>
        <text x="90" y="20" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="13" fill-opacity="0.6">G</text>
        <circle cx="70" cy="60" r="3" fill="#60a5fa" fill-opacity="0.6"/>
        <text x="60" y="56" text-anchor="end" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="10">a</text>
        <circle cx="110" cy="60" r="3" fill="#60a5fa" fill-opacity="0.6"/>
        <text x="120" y="56" text-anchor="start" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="10">b</text>
        <circle cx="90" cy="100" r="3" fill="#f59e0b" fill-opacity="0.6"/>
        <text x="90" y="118" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="10">a*b</text>

        <!-- Group H (right) -->
        <ellipse cx="310" cy="80" rx="70" ry="55" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.3"/>
        <text x="310" y="20" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="13" fill-opacity="0.6">H</text>
        <circle cx="290" cy="60" r="3" fill="#60a5fa" fill-opacity="0.6"/>
        <text x="280" y="56" text-anchor="end" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="10">f(a)</text>
        <circle cx="330" cy="60" r="3" fill="#60a5fa" fill-opacity="0.6"/>
        <text x="340" y="56" text-anchor="start" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="10">f(b)</text>
        <circle cx="310" cy="100" r="3" fill="#f59e0b" fill-opacity="0.6"/>
        <text x="310" y="118" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="10">f(a)*f(b)</text>

        <!-- Arrow f -->
        <line x1="165" y1="60" x2="278" y2="60" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.5"/>
        <polygon points="278,56 286,60 278,64" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.5"/>
        <text x="220" y="52" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="12" fill-opacity="0.5">f</text>

        <!-- Dashed arrow: f(a*b) = f(a)*f(b) -->
        <line x1="165" y1="100" x2="298" y2="100" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="4,3" stroke-opacity="0.3"/>
        <polygon points="298,96 306,100 298,104" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.3"/>
        <text x="220" y="95" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="9" fill-opacity="0.35">f(a*b) = f(a)*f(b)</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Homomorphism: f(a*b) = f(a)*f(b)
; Example: f: Z -> Z6, f(n) = n mod 6
; G = (Z, +), H = (Z6, + mod 6)

(define (f n) (modulo n 6))

; Check: f(a + b) = f(a) +6 f(b)
(define a 8)
(define b 15)

(display "f(a + b) = f(") (display (+ a b))
(display ") = ") (display (f (+ a b))) (newline)

(display "f(a) + f(b) mod 6 = ")
(display (modulo (+ (f a) (f b)) 6)) (newline)

; They match! The mod function is a homomorphism.
(display "Equal? ") (display (= (f (+ a b))
                                (modulo (+ (f a) (f b)) 6)))
`} />

    <div class="python-block my-2" style="display:none">
      <Repl client:visible initialCode={`# Homomorphism: Z -> Z6 via mod 6
f = lambda n: n % 6
a, b = 8, 15

print("f(a+b) = f(" + str(a+b) + ") = " + str(f(a+b)))
print("f(a)+f(b) mod 6 = " + str((f(a)+f(b)) % 6))
print("Equal? " + str(f(a+b) == (f(a)+f(b)) % 6))
`} />
    </div>


    <!-- 2. Kernel -->
    <h3>Kernel</h3>
    <p>The <strong>kernel</strong> of f is the set of elements that map to the identity: ker(f) = (a in G : f(a) = e_H). The kernel is always a subgroup of G. A homomorphism is injective if and only if its kernel is trivial (just the identity).</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Kernel of f: Z -> Z6, f(n) = n mod 6
; ker(f) = all integers n where n mod 6 = 0
; That is: ..., -12, -6, 0, 6, 12, ... = 6Z

(define (f n) (modulo n 6))

; Check a range
(display "Kernel elements in [-12..12]: ")
(let loop ((n -12))
  (when (<= n 12)
    (when (= (f n) 0)
      (display n) (display " "))
    (loop (+ n 1))))
(newline)

; The kernel is the subgroup 6Z of Z.
; It is isomorphic to Z itself.
(display "ker(f) = 6Z = multiples of 6")
`} />

    <div class="python-block my-2" style="display:none">
      <Repl client:visible initialCode={`# Kernel of f: Z -> Z6
f = lambda n: n % 6
kernel = [n for n in range(-12, 13) if f(n) == 0]
print("Kernel in [-12..12]: " + str(kernel))
print("ker(f) = 6Z = multiples of 6")
`} />
    </div>


    <!-- 3. Image -->
    <h3>Image</h3>
    <p>The <strong>image</strong> of f is the set of elements in H that are actually hit: im(f) = (f(a) : a in G). The image is always a subgroup of H. A homomorphism is surjective if its image is all of H.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Image of f: Z4 -> Z4, f(n) = 2n mod 4

(define (f n) (modulo (* 2 n) 4))

(display "f(0) = ") (display (f 0)) (newline)
(display "f(1) = ") (display (f 1)) (newline)
(display "f(2) = ") (display (f 2)) (newline)
(display "f(3) = ") (display (f 3)) (newline)

; Image = (0, 2). A subgroup of Z4.
; Not surjective (1 and 3 are not hit).
(display "Image = (0, 2)")
`} />

    <div class="python-block my-2" style="display:none">
      <Repl client:visible initialCode={`# Image of f: Z4 -> Z4, f(n) = 2n mod 4
f = lambda n: (2 * n) % 4

for n in range(4):
    print("f(" + str(n) + ") = " + str(f(n)))

image = sorted(set(f(n) for n in range(4)))
print("Image = " + str(image))
# Not surjective: 1 and 3 are not hit.
`} />
    </div>


    <!-- Notation -->
    <h3>Notation reference</h3>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-700">
            <th class="py-2 pr-4">Math</th>
            <th class="py-2 pr-4">Scheme</th>
            <th class="py-2 pr-4">Python</th>
            <th class="py-2">Meaning</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="font-mono">
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-4">f: G &rarr; H</td><td class="pr-4 text-green-300">(define (f x) ...)</td><td class="pr-4 text-blue-300">def f(x): ...</td><td class="font-sans">Homomorphism from G to H</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-4">ker(f)</td><td class="pr-4 text-green-300">(= (f x) 0)</td><td class="pr-4 text-blue-300">f(x) == 0</td><td class="font-sans">Elements mapping to identity</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-4">im(f)</td><td class="pr-4 text-green-300">(map f G)</td><td class="pr-4 text-blue-300">set(f(x) for x in G)</td><td class="font-sans">Elements in H that are hit</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4">f(ab) = f(a)f(b)</td><td class="pr-4 text-green-300">verified above</td><td class="pr-4 text-blue-300">verified above</td><td class="font-sans">Homomorphism property</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- Neighbors -->
    <Neighbors>

